    "inference_output": "A great example of how this perspective can be applied in real life is when you're preparing for an important job interview. You could be feeling nervous and anxious about the interview, and you might make a mistake during the interview that could potentially cost you the job. However, instead of beating yourself up over the mistake, you could focus on what you can learn from the experience. You could reflect on what went wrong, what you could have done differently, and how you can improve for the next interview.\nBy adopting this mindset, you can turn a potentially negative experience into a valuable learning opportunity. This can help you to become more confident and self-assured in your abilities, as you recognize that mistakes are a natural part of the learning process. Additionally, this perspective can help you to develop a growth mindset, where you see challenges as opportunities for growth and improvement, rather than as threats to your ego or self-worth.\nIn the long term, this approach can lead to greater success and happiness in your personal and professional life. By viewing mistakes as learning opportunities, you can develop a more resilient and adaptable mindset, which can help you to navigate through challenges and setbacks more effectively. This can lead to greater confidence, improved relationships, and a more fulfilling life overall.\n"
